  <ul class="comments by_rank" >
      
      <li class="ctsh clearfix" data-cid="17054779">
        <div class="ilst">
          <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/dora13/"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u2255032-25.jpg" alt="dora13" class="" /></a>
        </div>
        <div class="con">
          <div class="nlst">
            <h3>
              <div class="note-toggle rr">
                <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/17054779/" class="note-unfolder">展开</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/17054779/" class="">第67页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/dora13/" class=" " title="dora13">dora13</a>
                (I want everything on the table)
              
                <span class="allstar40" title="推荐"></span>
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="17054779">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">Schopenhauer maintains that each person's character is both constant and inborn. We can neither choose nor change what we are. We can be educated to understand the world and ourselves better, giving us better, more refined motives on which to act, but the self that these motives prompt into action really has not altered:&quot; Under the changeable shell of his years, hhis relationshhips, and even ...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2012-03-03 00:22</span>
                  
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="">2人喜欢</span>
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                <blockquote><q>Schopenhauer maintains that each person's character is both constant and inborn. We can neither choose nor change what we are. We can be educated to understand the world and ourselves better, giving us better, more refined motives on which to act, but the self that these motives prompt into action really has not altered:&quot; Under the changeable shell of his years, hhis relationshhips, and even his store of knowledge and opinions, there hides, like a crab under its shell, the identical and real man, quite unchangeble and always the same&quot; . Schopenhauer thinks that many of ordinary attitudes bear out this claim: we assume not just identity of the person, but constancy in the moral character as well. When we have gone on trusting someone to behave in a certain way, and have eventually been disappointed, &quot;We never say: &quot; His character has changed&quot;, but &quot;I was mistaken about him&quot;. </q></blockquote>
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







<div class="rec-sec">

    <span class="rec">

<a href="https://www.douban.com/accounts/register?reason=collect" class="j a_show_login lnk-sharing lnk-douban-sharing">推荐</a>
</span>
</div>

                  </div>
                <div class="pl col-time">
                  <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/17054779/#comments">回应</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;
                  2012-03-03 00:22
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </li>
      
      <li class="ctsh clearfix" data-cid="36042514">
        <div class="ilst">
          <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/SilentPenguin/"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u62177957-13.jpg" alt="⁧⁨⁩" class="" /></a>
        </div>
        <div class="con">
          <div class="nlst">
            <h3>
              <div class="note-toggle rr">
                <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/36042514/" class="note-unfolder">展开</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/36042514/" class="">第61页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/SilentPenguin/" class=" " title="⁧⁨⁩">⁧⁨⁩</a>
                (检身心于平日不可无忧勤惕厉工夫)
              
                <span class="allstar40" title="推荐"></span>
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="36042514">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <div class="ll">
                    <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/36042514/"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/small/public/p36042514-1.jpg"></a>
                  </div>
                  <span class="">这种对爱情的“亵渎”，简直惊世骇俗！自私的基因比之简直弱爆了… 1859年真是群星璀璨的一年，达尔文首次发表《物种起源》，叔本华更新发布第三版《意志与表象的世界》。在同时期的黑格尔，已经把传统西哲的理性，推高到多么走火入魔的境地时，叔却把性和意志拔到这么高的地位。哲学史自此被撕开了一个口子，这道口子越来越大，最终形成二十世纪非理性哲学的一脉滚滚洪流…</span>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/36042514/">(<span class="">1回应</span>)</a>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2015-09-03 20:48</span>
                  
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="">1人喜欢</span>
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                <div class="image-container image-float-center"><div class="image-wrapper"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/large/public/p36042514-1.jpg"></div></div><div class="image-container image-float-center"><div class="image-wrapper"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/large/public/p36042514-2.jpg"></div></div><div class="image-container image-float-center"><div class="image-wrapper"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/large/public/p36042514-3.jpg"></div></div><div class="image-container image-float-center"><div class="image-wrapper"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/large/public/p36042514-4.jpg"></div></div><p>这种对爱情的“亵渎”，简直惊世骇俗！自私的基因比之简直弱爆了…

1859年真是群星璀璨的一年，达尔文首次发表《物种起源》，叔本华更新发布第三版《意志与表象的世界》。在同时期的黑格尔，已经把传统西哲的理性，推高到多么走火入魔的境地时，叔却把性和意志拔到这么高的地位。哲学史自此被撕开了一个口子，这道口子越来越大，最终形成二十世纪非理性哲学的一脉滚滚洪流…</p>
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







